# What NOT to send to the Docker build. The image ships one Go binary; everything listed
# here is either not Go, or not needed to compile it.
#
# This file is what lets the Dockerfile say `COPY . .` instead of naming each package. The
# Dockerfile used to enumerate them — cache/, cluster/, node/, ring/, cmd/ — which is a
# second source of truth about what packages exist, and it is only ever checked in
# production. Adding notify/ broke the deploy: the build stage could not see the directory,
# and `go build` failed with "no required module provides package .../notify".
.git/
.gitignore
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
render.yaml
README.md
CLAUDE.md

frontend/
docs/
logs/
bin/
